  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Since 1995, together with many longstanding partner organizations, churches, and individuals, Christian Friends of Korea has sent more than $80 million worth of goods to people in need in North Korea. Christian Friends of Korea sends food, medicine, agricultural supplies and equipment, bedding and blankets, medical equipment and supplies and other goods needed in tuberculosis and hepatitis hospitals and sanitoria in North Korea. The organization makes bi-annual visits to ensure the aid goes to the intended staff and patients at these facilities and to work side-by-side with North Koreans on projects including renovation of multiple health care facilities, installation of medical equipment, solar powered water or lighting projects, water well drilling, greenhouse building, medical staff training, and more.</narrative>
  </description>
